  <p>
    The one-day-only live painting performance featured a series of
    canvases and digitally developed copper casts. Installed primarily in
    a chicken coop, the works by Kenny Schachter, Maura and Margaret—a
    pair of <em>Gallus gallus domesticus</em>—are available to view by
    appointment through June 21, 2025.
  </p>
  <p>
    The exhibition draws on Rudolf Stingel's Celotex insulation panel works. Here, chickens collaborated on micro-canvases
    using edible glue and seed. The resulting works were scanned and will
    later be cast in silver and gold.
  </p>

